of the\ntheory is not completely clear at this point in time. But the non-metric part\nof the theory may be tested rather independently. That is, the theory predicts\nthat gravitational fields in vacuum and gravitationally bound bodies made of\nideal gas expand like the expansion of the Universe. Several observations\nsuggest this; e.g., the \"Pioneer effect\", the mean acceleration of the Moon,\nthe spin-down of the Earth, palaeo-tidal records, etc. Thus quasi-metric\nrelativity has experimental support where metric theories fail.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 30 Nov 2001 02:42:02 GMT"},{"version":"v10","created":"Fri, 11 Feb 2005 07:51:41 GMT"},{"version":"v11","created":"Thu, 16 Jun 2005 23:33:18 GMT"},{"version":"v12","created":"Tue, 6 Dec 2005 05:11:52 GMT"},{"version":"v13","created":"Fri, 9 May 2014 16:08:26 GMT"},{"version":"v14","created":"Sat, 23 Mar 2019 09:47:49 GMT"},{"version":"v15","created":"Thu, 19 Mar 2020 11:45:11 GMT"},{"version":"v16","created":"Mon, 28 Dec 2020 23:16:54 GMT"},{"version":"v17","created":"Tue, 31 Jan 2023 10:39:15 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 10 Dec 2001 22:07:47 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 31 Jan 2002 20:04:09 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Thu, 7 Mar 2002 03:06:43 GMT"},{"version":"v5","created":"Sat, 4 May 2002 17:14:50 GMT"},{"version":"v6","created":"Wed, 12 Mar 2003 00:10:45 GMT"},{"version":"v7","created":"Fri, 7 Nov 2003 18:27:42 GMT"},{"version":"v8","created":"Tue, 30 Mar 2004 02:30:23 GMT"},{"version":"v9","created":"Wed, 14 Apr 2004 17:13:43 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-02-01"}
